From 18bfe80e0372c372bd4e3fe22370ed44058ba25b Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Devin AI <158243242+devin-ai-integration[bot]@users.noreply.github.com>
Date: Thu, 16 Apr 2026 02:18:33 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] feat: Phase 1 Foundation - Wazuh Desktop Agent

Implements the foundational architecture for the Wazuh Desktop Agent (WDA),
a lightweight, Rust-based security agent optimized for desktops, laptops, and VMs.

Cargo workspace with 10 crates:
- wda-core: Agent lifecycle, config engine (YAML), signal handling
- wda-pal: Platform Abstraction Layer with cross-platform filesystem watcher
- wda-event-bus: Async broadcast channel with priority support
- wda-comms: Wazuh protocol v5 (AES-256-CBC, TCP/UDP, enrollment)
- wda-fim, wda-logcollector, wda-inventory, wda-sca,
  wda-active-response, wda-rootcheck: Module stubs for Phase 2

Key features:
- Event-driven filesystem watching via notify crate (inotify/FSEvents/RDCW)
- AES-256-CBC encryption with SHA-256 key derivation
- Wazuh authd enrollment protocol (port 1515)
- TCP connection manager with exponential backoff reconnection
- Power-aware adaptive scheduling (5 profiles)
- Cross-platform system info collection (Linux /proc, /sys, /etc)
- Zero warnings: passes cargo fmt, cargo clippy

Co-Authored-By: ken <ken@uney.com>
